      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): force re-login flag, remediation hint, and session-scoped fallback skip cache",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `openclaw models auth login --force` so operators can drop cached provider auth profiles before starting the existing provider auth flow.\n- Add auth-class failover remediation hints that produce shell-safe recovery commands through the shared CLI formatter.\n- Add a session-scoped fallback skip cache for non-primary auth failures. It is disabled by default; operators opt in with `OPENCLAW_FALLBACK_SKIP_TTL_MS`, clamped to `[1s, 10m]`.\n- Keep web-search provider validation on the shared install-catalog resolver so config validation and setup use one source of truth.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `--force` purges cached provider auth profiles only after a valid auth method is resolved; auth failover summaries include a formatted recovery command; opted-in fallback skip state is keyed by `(sessionId, provider, model)` and causes the second turn to skip the same non-primary auth-failing candidate while preserving the primary attempt.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local Ubuntu 24.04 / WSL2 checkout, Node v24.15.0, branch `fix/auth-relogin-and-skip-known-bad-fallbacks`. Final head is `6d044f3e14`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```\npnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/config/validation.ts src/agents/failover-error.ts src/agents/failover-error.test.ts src/agents/fallback-skip-cache.ts src/agents/fallback-skip-cache.test.ts src/agents/model-fallback.ts src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts src/config/config.web-search-provider.test.ts docs/gateway/authentication.md docs/concepts/model-failover.md\npnpm exec oxlint src/config/validation.ts src/config/config.web-search-provider.test.ts src/agents/failover-error.test.ts src/agents/failover-error.ts src/agents/fallback-skip-cache.test.ts src/agents/fallback-skip-cache.ts src/agents/model-fallback.ts src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts\ngit diff --check\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/fallback-skip-cache.test.ts src/agents/failover-error.test.ts src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts src/commands/models/auth.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts -t \"uses the opt-in auth skip cache on the second turn\" --reporter=verbose\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```\nTest Files  6 passed (6)\nTests       284 passed (284)\n\n✓ |agents-core| src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts > runWithModelFallback > uses the opt-in auth skip cache on the second turn for the same session\n✓ |agents-support| src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts > runWithModelFallback > uses the opt-in auth skip cache on the second turn for the same session\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests       2 passed | 144 skipped (146)\n\ngit diff --check\nDIFF_CHECK_EXIT:0\n\npnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/config/validation.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\nOXFMT_EXIT:0\n\npnpm exec oxlint src/config/validation.ts\nOXLINT_EXIT:0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The second turn still attempts the primary `openai/gpt-5.4`, skips the previously auth-failing non-primary `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7`, records a synthetic skipped attempt containing `recent auth failure`, then succeeds on `google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview`. The final config cleanup removes the parallel web-search install catalog scan from `src/config/validation.ts` and routes validation through the shared catalog resolver.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live OAuth re-auth against a real provider, because that requires interactive credentials.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 ...`\n- [x] `pnpm exec oxlint ...`\n- [x] `git diff --check`\n- [x] Targeted vitest suite for changed auth/fallback seams\n- [x] Focused second-turn fallback skip regression\n- [ ] Live OAuth re-auth round trip\n",
        "branch": "fix/auth-relogin-and-skip-known-bad-fallbacks",
        "head_sha": "d259217eacca0705fd598271250c689386a4b452",
